  "prompt": "What is the Tinder like limit?",
  "response": "Tinder, like many other social platforms, imposes certain limits to ensure user safety and promote genuine interactions. Here are some key limits on Tinder:\n\n1. **Swipes per Day**:\n   - Free users: Tinder limits the number of \"likes\" (swipes right) you can make in a 12-hour period. The exact number can vary but is typically around 100 likes in 24 hours.\n   - Paid users (Tinder Plus, Gold, or Platinum): The swipe limit is significantly higher or removed entirely, depending on the subscription tier.\n\n2. **Super Likes**:\n   - Free users: Usually get 1 Super Like per day.\n   - Paid users: Get additional Super Likes based on their subscription plan (e.g., Tinder Plus offers 5 per week, while Tinder Gold offers 5 per day).\n\n3. **Messages**:\n   - You can only message someone if you've matched with them. There's no limit to the number of messages you can send to a match.\n\n4. **Boosts**:\n   - Free users: Typically get 1 free Boost per month.\n   - Paid users: Get additional Boosts depending on their subscription tier.\n\n5. **Profile Edits**:\n   - There\u2019s no strict limit to how often you can edit your profile, but frequent changes might prompt a temporary restriction to ensure the account is being used legitimately.\n\n6. **Match Limits**:\n   - Free users: No hard limit on the number of matches, but the swipe limit indirectly affects how many people you can match with.\n   - Paid users: No match limits.\n\nThese limits are subject to change based on Tinder\u2019s policies and updates. If you're hitting a limit, consider upgrading to a paid subscription for more flexibility.",
